## In Popular Culture

Rajiv Gandhi's life and assassination have inspired various films and documentaries. Notable works include *India's Rajiv*, a documentary series by [Simi Garewal](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simi_Garewal), and feature films such as *The Terrorist* (1997) and *Madras Cafe* (2013). These portrayals contribute to the ongoing examination of his impact on Indian society and politics.

